"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d368ed",
"children":[
"If the patient is hemodynamically unstable, provide resuscitation before diagnostic studies are performed."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f7b2fa",
"children":[
"Transfusion management is the same as for UGI bleeding, as are decisions regarding discontinuation and/or reversal of anticoagulant and antiplatelet agents."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"beab1d",
"children":[
"Select colonoscopy within 24 hours of admission for hemodynamically stable patients without rapid bleeding."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7e05f9",
"children":[
"For hemodynamically unstable patients following resuscitation or ongoing bleeding:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b071e9",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"computed tomography angiography",
"children":[
"CTA"
]
},
" "
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2b35b9",
"children":[
"catheter-based embolization if CTA positive"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d76b9e",
"children":[
"upper endoscopy if CTA negative"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0e7522",
"children":[
"Ten percent of rapid rectal bleeding has a UGI source."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
